commit.message: CI: test with mininimal set of packages loaded

Correction for SMALL_AVAILABLE_FUNCS[11]

The sglppow package was hot-patching this already for some time.

build: remove incorrect +x bit on .g files

Our rpmlint run warns of:

gap-smallgrp.noarch: E: spurious-executable-perm (Badness: 50)
/usr/share/gap/pkg/SmallGrp-1.5.1/id10/idgrp10.g.gz
gap-smallgrp.noarch: E: spurious-executable-perm (Badness: 50)
/usr/share/gap/pkg/SmallGrp-1.5.1/id9/idgrp9.g.gz

UnbindGlobal -> UNBIND_GLOBAL

This silences a warning if the globals being unbound are no defined.
This in turn is crucial for allowing us to eventually get rid of
the dummy declarations for these functions within the GAP library.
PackageInfo.g: link to Mathjax manual by default
Correct number of groups of order 2^10

Replace GAP Team as maintainer by myself

This was requested by Bettina

CI: Ensure code coverage reporting will work in February 2022 and beyond

See https://github.com/gap-actions/process-coverage/issues/10
Switch CI to use GitHub Actions
Document NrSmallGroups; mark some synonyms as obsolete
